text: Mo Sun-Young (born 11 March 1973) is a South Korean taekwondo athlete. She competed at the 1992 Summer Olympics, where taekwondo was a demonstration sport, in the finweight event. At the Asian Taekwondo Championships she became Asian Champion in 1992 after winning the bronze medal in 1990. == References == == Other websites == * Category:1973 births Category:Living people Category:South Korean taekwondo practitioners
